See this is why I consider LTT to be half baked sell outs. There is no such thing as a privacy protecting browser. Yes you can encrypt the actual requests between your browser and the websites you visit, but the websites still get your data! What data do you actually think they are collecting? It's your IP address and what websites it visits, not you as an individual, but you as a statistic. How the hell would more encryption stop that?

And then to suggest that a VPN is better? A VPN collects your data just as much google does. Your just changing the person collecting it to someone less regulated and who straight up lies.

Amateur hour I swear

snippet.textDisplay:
You must be really naive to believe, that doh in Firefox will give you any more privacy. Alone the fact, that the dns requests will be handeled by cloudflare, is enough for me to surely not use it. At the very least, my isp is bound to the laws in my country and the agencies in my country are still way too incompetent to make actual use of the huge amount of dns traffic, that the population is creating. Btw. cloudflare will sell those data for sure... or at the very least make sure to “loose” them.

Edit: btw. Think about it, is it really a good idea to collect such data in a single bucket or isn’t it better to distribute it over a lot of buckets, if you value privacy ;)

I have the Xperia 1 1 I guess it'd be called now, it's a nice phone, I mainly picked it because it was using the snapdragon 855 chipset like the samsung Galaxys, whilst everything else was using the 845. It also has no notch or holepunch in the screen. The battery lasts ages and it comes with a usb C to 3.5mm jack adaptor so the lack of a headphone jack isn't so bad. The 21 by 9 screen is great for things like facebook or any long scrolling page (forums etc) or for films, but pretty trash for everything else. Many apps fails to render properly on it.

The sony UI is also pretty terrible compared to stock android or even Samsungs

Will give the 1 2 a look though maybe they have sorted some of these problems.
